caption: Do to I work! The environment is beautiful. It's the place to be!
Decent vegetarian&vegan options. The tofu Banh Mi was the best. Minimum $7 on cards.

Made me spend extra money to meet a ridiculous card minimum. They literally made it difficult for me to spend my money there. Place was empty. I’m never going back.
Pita Pizza was good. The tacos were a bit cold, but we were mostly glad they keep their kitchen open pretty late if not the entire time they're open. Bartender and cook were very friendly.
Tots and a semblance of peace among the chaos. Can't argue with that.

The soup came in styrofoam and the crackers were individually wrapped in plastic packaging. Not eco-friendly and the vegan chili was just alright, nothing special. But I do applaud them for having vegetarian/vegan options labeled on the menu.

I visited a lot of places in New Orleans but this place...is amazing. I ordered the Tofu Bahn Mi and it was so good I almost married the sandwich. also, the bartender is adorable and so good at what she does. Friendly vibes, good good, and beautiful wall art.
Frozen Irish coffee alone is worth it the trip
Got drunk and pizza good

I went here tonight and thought it was great! The atmosphere was friendly, casual, and the employees were fun to talk to. I chatted with Erin or Aaron, one of the cooks and had a great time discussing football and New Orleans in general.  I got the tofu bahn mi and it was absolutely delicious! My sister got the loaded potatoes and she loved  hers too. There's a ton of vegetarian and vegan options here. The frozen Irish coffee is a must have for a dessert.
Tachos. The best!
Good food (boudin bhan mi), good drinks (frozen Irish coffee), and friendly staff.

Excellent sandwiches. Lots of vegetarian and meat options! Quick service so it can be a low key dinner spot.
The bar tenders are really polite and attentive
I wish I had a picture, but if you are a fan of spicy food, please try their crawfish boudin. It's to die for.

Very clean bar with a open style kitchen and quick service. I love that they still have a pay phone because they are almost extinct. The bartender seemed slightly off standish for some reason but was fast to serve. The place was mostly empty while we were there and I didn't try any of the food.

The atmosphere at 13 is fun and approachable. It is small, but not cramped, and has a dive bar vibe that leans trendy. The food came out quickly, and was quite good, although maybe a tad overpriced. The bar tender was nice and efficient, with a slightly gruff demeanor that did not come across as rude. The drinks were good and not over priced, but don't come here looking for fancy, signature cocktails. 13 is in a great location, and is perfectly in line with the vibe of the neighborhood. I would recommend stopping in for a drink and a bite. It's a great place to take a load off and relax with a couple friends.
Excellent food! While visiting New Orleans I struggled finding decent vegetarian options. This place was absolutely fantastic, even for my non-vegetarian family. I recommend the BBQ tofu sandwhich!
should put that no one under 21 can come on the website .
This is a great place to stop on. The food was awesome. First time there. I would go again.
Love 13.
(Translated by Google) TACHOS  (Original) TACHOS

Great place to get a drink and VEGAN FOOD! Vegan/vegetarian food can be a little tricky to find in New Orleans, but we scored big time with 13. The baked tots are a pure delight as are the BBQ tofu sandwich, tofu banh mi, mushroom philly and the tofu garden wrap (we had a few nights' stay in NOLA, so this was our dinner spot the whole time). Friendly staff, well priced drinks and food, funky spot, plus they're open 4 pm to 4 am!

We would really like to eat here, however, when we tried to make a large pickup order, we were put on hold indefinitely. After 15 mins we hung up and ordered from somewhere else. Bummer. I hope they hire a hostess or something to take orders over the phone.

Nice chill setting not to much seating. I ordered my food to go vegan tater tots, my thoights, I found a new food dish with the vegan BBQ tofu sandwich was perfect. Order was done right and received a discount for calling directly to the restaurant and placing an order for pickup, sheesh don't tell everybody lol. And the red wine was spot on to finish off the meal. Open from 4pm to 4am. Perfect New Orleans late night spot for vegans or non vegans.
Lots of veggy tasty options and a good beer selection!
Delicious! One of their signature drinks. You have to try it while you're in NOLA. Tastes like a milkshake! 😄
Dive bar that is open until they close.

A great late-night dive.  I stopped by twice on a NOLA visit earlier this year. It's a calm spot for between (or after) visiting the bustling clubs nearby. The drinks are cheap, the staff are nice, and the food is the kind that will make you really, really happy after a night of alcohol. Or just to sate late-night hangries.  Try the boudin bahn-mi, you'll thank me later.  Late night / after-hours venues often end up with staff that are crabby from dealing with hot-mess people all the time. Not here, they were nice even to people slurring so badly it was comical.  This is a rare gem, and provides essential parts of the late-night NOLA experience-- somewhere "else" to go, and somewhere to get food.
No live music but one of the best bars for drinking in NOLA..thank you !!
Ah gotta love it
Yummy tater tots and awesome beer selection
Great drinks and atmosphere.  Outstanding food.  Bartenders are awesome!
Try the Curry tachos! Also the frozen Irish coffees. Well worth it!

Just ate here. I had the vegan banh mi. It was absolutely fabulous. The 3 star rating is because of everything else that happened during my short visit.  When I got the check, I was surprised to find out that there was an extra charge of $1.5 (!!) for the vegan mayo. I was not informed that this charge would be coming when the bartender so kindly informed me of the substitution possibility.  If you're going to charge that much for a substitution - which you absolutely shouldn't do - you need to inform the patrons while they order. The bartender's response of "I don't pick the prices" is hardly an excuse - nor is it an appropriate thing to say when a patron communicates their dismay after you asked them if they enjoyed the food (I said "yes, absolutely", but that the surprise charge did not sit well with me).  On top of that, I found out later - your bathroom doesn't lock and had no soap dispenser: the latter is hardly a good sign in an astablishment that serves food and at which, I assume, the people handling the food also relieve themselves sometimes.  After the bartender's poor and defensive behavior earlier, I didn't really feel like saying anything to her. Seemed like she wasn't keen on receiving negative feedback, constructive or otherwise.  It's too bad that this is the taste I left with, because the food was really great and your chefs / cooks absolutely deserve applause for their work!
Good ambiance. Cool place

Seriously need to work on everything when it comes to dining in. I understand it's a bar but the food was mediocre (how do you mess up plain tots), just from watching you can tell they're guessing whose order just came out even though there's tables, the bar tender is having to take care of the whole restaurant drinks/food orders/bringing out food and I had to check twice to get my side with my entree (first time they didn't make the tots, second time who knows) I feel bad for the staff because there just is no system.
We got the vegan chili and it was literally just black beans?? But the people were nice and the place was coool
Great bartender, Ashley, great pricing. Love this place.

We went in not sure what to expect, because we'd seen conflicting reviews. Well, I'm here to tell you this place is amazing! We both ordered the BBQ sandwich which came with house-made cashew mayo (so good) and a veganized order of the tatchos. The portions were huge and the staff was super kind. Plus, afterward we got to walk outside and hear a jazz show. Great location and great food!
Loved this place for the vegan food options!  We came here a few times during our stay in NOLA and loved it.  Great red beans and rice, vegan totchos, cold drinks and great service!  A+
Cool place and tons of options
Love 13. We don't understand why the menu has changed so much. We don t go there as much for that reason.

Didn't eat here but watched the wait staff, and kitchen staff execute perfectly. The drinks were good and priced accordingly, considering they had a live band there. I'll be back soon.

Affordable drinks. Staff behind the bar are very friendly and welcoming.
This place opens at 12 noon.

Wasn't really impressed, in fact we were disappointed. Now that being said we went on a Friday night and they seemed under staffed as it was. The main problem was the quality or lack thereof our food. First both of our meals came out lukewarm. My wife got a breakfast sandwich which was okay but nothing special for 8 dollars. She said it was just bland and after trying it I agreed. I got the loaded baked potato tachos. (Tater tot dish like nachos, cool concept so I was excited). They were terrible. The tots were so overcooked it was a workout to chew. The cheese was practically burnt plastic. The biggest complaint was the dish itself was so overcooked it was glued to the tinfoil. When trying to remove it from the foil I had to scrape and pry it loose, the foil would tear and I would still have to peel off what foil I could.  I ended up not finishing the meal after the first few jaw destroying bites. Im sure I could have asked to have it remade but to order or get service you had to the bar and try and catch someone's attention but it was almost impossible and even more people had arrived and we didn't have time to wait and my jaw hurt. Plus it just didn't even taste good enough to make me think it was an accident. The staff were friendly and the pumpkin pie drinks were good enough to redeem this to a two star review but we were just super disappointed by the food.

I waited 15 mins. A few larger tops came in and I got constantly  to the back of the line. The bartender seemed to classify your value as a patron. Based on how big your party was and how much you would tip. Unfortunate. Hope things work out for them with this philosophy.

I saw some pictures of the sandwich before coming and my looks the same and taste the same as I was imaging. really tasty, specially the dijon mustard and the vegan mayo. This spot comes up as an essential spot for vegetarians. I get it, they do have a decent selection of vegetarian food, but it isn't overwhelming or anything. Our bartender was spectacular. He was attentive, and fast. He made a killer Bloody Mary, as well. The Bloody Mary here was one of the better ones in the city I've had the pleasure of trying. The tachos were definitely a great late night snack. Tv was a little bright inside for my personal taste.

Stop the bologna...lol Darrell made me a frozen Irish coffee with abita root beer and a Jameson floater OMG u better get it or it missing out. You need to get TFOH its unbelievable. It's something I'd never think of on my own, and looks "interesting" but well worth the adventurous spirit it takes to dive in. Staff was very friendly, and they're open super late (kitchen closes at 3:30am!). Added to my Must Visit List whenever I'm in NOLA.
Great service and the tofu sandwich was delicious. If your vegan I definitely recommend this place.

Chill environment, bar food and vegan options as well. Open late for folks who like to bar crawl. 10/10 will return and they got tots.

I’m actually very disappointed to have to write this review. As someone who is vegan and never been to this state, you wanna find vegan options that are close by.and not have to travel far. This place offered vegan options that sounded ok ( Philadelphia is better) and I waited 1hour to get a “ vegan mushroom cheesesteak”. Look I am a line cook myself, I get the stress y’all get when it’s busy. But, I was watching them work the whole time and all the orders were TOTS. why is it taking long to make mushrooms? Pre cook some if you know you’re going to get slammed. I wanted to go back there and train the staff myself.  After waiting a hour for my food, I picked up and left and wasn’t waiting anyone. The staff started screaming at me and I told them I don’t want it and they had the bouncer run after me and grabbed me AFTER I SAID I did not want it.the bartenders started cursing and acting like kids. No manger on duty? Most likely. If you are vegan they’re other places to eat. I don’t recommend this at all. It’s not even 100% vegan so you can’t trust if they don’t change their gloves or not. Never again.
Boudin Banh Mi was amazing! They also had a Vietnamese coffee beer and Frozen Irish Coffee, both amazing and strong :)
New place

Late night eats while bar hopping. Service was OK as it took awhile to get our drinks out. Literally, just water ... we ordered vegan chili and it was DELISH! Tots smothered in barbacoa and the  bacon chicken wrap were pretty tasty and filling.

NOLA was the first stop of my 3,000-mile road trip from Atlanta to San Francisco. We were starving and this was the first place that popped up when we searched on Yelp. We found parking a couple blocks away and ran through the heavy rain to get to 13. The interior decor was awesome, ill post pics. We were the only people in the restaurant so service was fast and good. I ordered the Philly Sandwich, Tots for 2 and a Diet Coke. Diet Coke was on tap from the bar and it was quite flat and not that good. The Philly Sandwich was good but had too little meat for the amount of bread. The tots were good but I think they left them in the fryer too long since they came out extra crispy.  Diet Coke: 4/10 (Drinkable) Philly sandwich: 5/10 (sparse on the meat) Tots: 7/10 (Too Crispy)
When other kitchens are closed, they stay open with great food options.  Easy, nice people, and reasonable pricing.
Bbq tofu sandwiches!  Open late and everyone who has served us has been so nice (we have been here three nights in a row).  Quite a few vegan options.
An ok bar where you can get ok drinks and eat ok food. It's location on Frenchmen and it's late night hours are it's best features.
Greeeeeeat service, even better food! A must-stop for vegetarians and vegans in NOLA.
The food was legit!!

so good and vegan/veggie friendly. also good drinks. don’t miss this place, it will change your life

VEGAN FRIENDLY!! YES A LATE NIGHT VEGAN FRIENDLY BAR WITH FULL SERVICE ON FRENCHMAN!!!! I could not ask for more, ate here twice both after 2am and it was delicious. I had the BBQ tofu sandwich the first night and the tofu banh mi the second time. The staff working was Micheal and he really put a cherry on an amazing experience!

I ordered for 13 Bar food from Grubhub.  The restaurant was electronically delivered the correct menu item but did not pay close enough attention.  They gave me a REAL BEEF Reuben sandwich instead of a TOFU Reuben, which is kind of a big deal to a vegetarian.  The restaurant wanted me to drive over (I'm in town on business) and swap out the sandwich.  Grubhub wanted to refund only the sandwich and have me pay ANOTHER delivery fee if I wanted the right sandwich.  The whole experience was a frustrating and expensive waste of time.
One word: Tachos. Do it. Tator tots covered in a variety of delicious toppings. Also, don't order their amazing rueben, because I want them all for myself.

First time in New Orleans, we saw a video that featured this place and decided to check it out. When I sat down I asked the bartender if he could make a hurricane and he said he would "look up" the ingredients. Later he brought me the supposed hurricane drink that I never even asked him to make and said "it's almost a hurricane, its just missing some ingredients" I gave it a try and it was awful. Meanwhile, we ordered some of their tots and were brought the wrong order! I didn't realize it was the wrong order until AFTER I took a bite. The guy came over and said he gave us the other tables order, he then picked up the dish that had the fork I ate off of and gave it to another person! Disgusting. He let another patron eat the tots that we took a bite out of with the fork that was eaten off of! The health department needs to check this place out ASAP. He even had the nerve to charge me for the drink! I've been ALL OVER the country and this is byfar the WORST experience I have ever had! I wouldn't recommend this place to anyone. BEWARE.
The Vegan Chilli Tatchos are so good.
Breakfast burrito is one of the best I've ever had. Ordered a side of pasta salad, it's great, but didn't need it. Burrito enough to fill this 6'3" 230lb man.

Cool bartender and chill, laid back vibe.  My pulled pork sandwich was pretty awful, but it could have just been a bad night or something.  Still would come back due to the great atmosphere.

I love the BLT and it's great to get something late at night. Other food is also good. It's pretty low key compared to the clubs and venues around and is nice if you want to get a bite or just chill and have a drink.

Great laid back bar in the middle of a busy block full of live music! The food is good and the bar staff is cool as heck! It's one of my celebrating spots. Cheers! I stopped in on my first night in NOLA because my tour guide earlier in the day raved about the tater tots. I had the Srirachos tots w/o chicken and wasn't overly impressed. I like my tots hot and crispy, these were warm and very soft. I did like the toppings on them and I loved the cocktail I had, Pimm's Cup. Service was fast and friendly. I wished the tots were better I would have rated a 5.

Bartender Louisa sucked balls. Tater tots, however, did not. Piss off Louisa, you ruined a great spot.

Honestly awful.  I seldom write reviews, but the food made both my girlfriend and I sick.  I'm vegan, so I thought I'd try the vegan tofu bbq sandwich per another reviewer, which was awful- a couple of pieces of cold tofu on a bland french bread, slathered in generic bbq sauce.  The Tachos are similarly uninspiring- the 'vegan chili' was half a can of plain black beans poured on top of lukewarm tater tots. My girlfriend initially liked her mushroom philly, but then said it gave her cramps and made her want to vomit.  Vegans and vegetarians, go elsewhere.  The server/bartender was completely indifferent (they were not busy at all at 7pm), and paid no attention to us while chitchatting with her friend.  The only thing this place has going for it is that it's open until 4 am.  I guess if you're wasted, starving to death, and in the quarter, it might be of use, but otherwise...pass this one by.
Drinks were strong and not expensive. Food was ok to soak up some of the booze from a night of drinking. Nothing special but pretty good. We were hungry and Izakaya was packed.
